This paper discusses the development of tools to analyze the behavior of probabilistic models, which are commonly used in machine learning applications such as generative models, sequence to sequence models, and models over functional spaces. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision). The paper also discusses the verification of these models, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
